  "prompt": "Is six hours of sleep enough for a 10-year-old?",
  "response": "No, six hours of sleep is generally not enough for a 10-year-old. The American Academy of Sleep Medicine recommends that children aged 6 to 12 years should get 9 to 12 hours of sleep per night for optimal health and development. Insufficient sleep can impact a child's mood, cognitive function, and overall well-being. It is important for parents and caregivers to ensure that children receive adequate sleep to support their growth and learning.",
